		{
			"content": {
				"id": "RLSA-2021:3440",
				"title": "Moderate: kernel-rt security and bug fix update",
				"description": "The kernel-rt packages provide the Real Time Linux Kernel, which enables fine-tuning for systems with extremely high determinism requirements.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* kernel: slab-out-of-bounds access in xdr_set_page_base() in net/sunrpc/xdr.c (CVE-2021-38201)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nBug Fix(es):\n\n* OSLAT spikes on subset of cpus (BZ#1986063)\n\n* kernel-rt: update RT source tree to the Rocky Linux-8.4.z source tree (BZ#1990013)\n\n* Failure to enter full_nohz due to needless SCHED softirqs (BZ#1990272)\n\n* kernel-rt: Make rcu_normal_after_boot writable (BZ#1995431)",
